    "body": "This PR fixes an incorrect LoRA B weight loading in fused_moe.py that caused vLLM LoRA outputs to diverge from PEFT/Transformers.\n\n## Purpose\n\nIn vLLM, the LoRA B weight for MoE layers was assumed to have shape (output_dim, num_experts, rank), while PEFT defines it as (output_dim, rank, num_experts). This mismatch prevents vLLM results from fully aligning with Transformers when loading PEFT-trained adapters.\n\nThis PR fixes the mismatch in `fused_moe` LoRA layers. Specifically, it corrects the expected shape of LoRA B weights to ensure vLLM is aligned with the [PEFT implementation](https://github.com/huggingface/peft/blob/261366de2e40cde64b702d6b9c527081ad850549/src/peft/tuners/lora/layer.py#L2094).\n\n## Test Plan\n\nI conducted a test using the `gpt-oss-20b` model with the `jeeejeee/gpt-oss-20b-lora-adapter-text2sql` adapter on the **Spider dataset**.\n\n**Quantitative Results (100 Samples):**\n\n* **vLLM Main Branch (Before Fix):** **0/100** samples matched the Transformers output.\n* **vLLM with this PR (After Fix):** **98/100** samples perfectly match the Transformers output.\n  *(The remaining 2% are likely due to minor floating-point precision, but the functional correctness is restored.)*\n\n**Qualitative Examples:**\n\n| Source                      | Output Consistency                                                                                                           |\n| :-------------------------- | :--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Transformers (Expected)** | `SELECT avg(Working_Horses) FROM farm WHERE Total_Horses > 5000`, `SELECT max(Cows) , min(Cows) FROM farm`, `SELECT max(Cows) , min(Cows) FROM farm`                   |\n| **vLLM (Main branch)**      | `SELECT AVG(Working_Horses) FROM farm WHERE Total_Horses > 5000;`, `SELECT MAX(Cows) AS Max_Cows, MIN(Cows) AS Min_Cows FROM farm;`, `SELECT MAX(Cows) AS Max_Cows, MIN(Cows) AS Min_Cows FROM farm;` |\n| **vLLM (This PR)**          | **Matches Transformers exactly.**                                                                                            |\n\nAfter applying this fix, the output from vLLM is now identical to the baseline Transformers/PEFT implementation.\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
